Diagnosis.
Body black (
Fig. 9
); two basal antennomere of antenna brownish yellow; mandible and palpi yellow; third antennomere (including annellus) 1.3 × longer than fourth antennomere (
Fig. 10G
); eye in dorsal view 1.6 × as long as temple (
Fig. 10I
); eye in lateral view 1.1 × higher than wide (
Fig. 10K
); frons smooth posteriorly, but rugose between antennal sockets; vertex and temple smooth (
Fig. 10I
); face weakly rugose medially, twice wider than high, rather convex medially, with a medio-longitudinal ridge (
Fig. 10J
); clypeus small, semi-elliptical and with some punctures (
Fig. 10J
); precoxal sulcus narrowly crenulated and small, not reaching middle coxa and anterior edge of epicnemial area (
Fig. 10C
); notauli incomplete, only present anteriorly; medioposterior depression deep and droplet-shaped, remaining far from middle of mesoscutum (
Fig. 10D
); surface of propodeum densely reticulate-rugose, areola absent posteriorly (
Fig. 10E
); pterostigma 5.0 × longer than its maximum width (
Fig. 10A
); hind coxa smooth (
Fig. 10N
); length of first tergite 1.3 × its apical width, its surface longitudinally striate and some rugae between striae, its dorsal carinae connected subposteriorly (
Fig. 10E
); ovipositor sheath with very few setae and only apically present; convexity of upper valve of ovipositor steep basally; total visible sheath 0.3 × as long as fore wing, and nearly as long as hind tibia (
Fig. 10H
); metasoma except first tergite dark reddish brown; legs yellowish brown, but apical part of hind tibia brown (
Fig. 9
).

Head. Transverse, width of head 2.0 × its lateral length, and 1.5 × wider than mesoscutum (
Fig. 10I
); antenna with 34 antennomere, third antennomere (including annellus) 1.3 × longer than fourth antennomere, length of third, fourth and penultimate antennomere 4.0, 4.0 and 2.2 × their width, respectively (
Fig. 10G
); maxillary palp incomplete (
Fig. 10K
); eye in dorsal view 1.6 × as long as temple (
Fig. 10I
); eye in lateral view 1.1 × higher than wide (
Fig. 10K
); frons smooth posteriorly, but rugose between antennal sockets (
Fig. 10I
); vertex and temple smooth (
Fig. 10I
); OOL:diameter of ocellus:POL= 13:5:6; face weakly rugose in middle, twice wider than high and with a medio-longitudinal ridge (
Fig. 10J
); clypeus small, semi-elliptical and with some punctures; mandible enlarged apically, dorsal tooth enlarged, lobe-shaped (
Fig. 10L
), ventral tooth medium-sized and lobe-shaped (
Fig. 10M
), middle tooth curved and acute, with no incision between first and second tooth (
Fig. 10L
), medial length of mandible 1.4 × its maximum width.

